== Per-principal ingress routing: client cert SAN decides the tenant server ==
   (Envoy terminates mTLS, derives principal from the cert URI-SAN, routes on it.)

cert 'tenant_a':  HTTP 200   x-routed-to=spark-connect-tenant-a
            server response: Spark Connect request completed without asserting a user_id that matches the verified principal 'tenant_a'
cert 'tenant_b':  HTTP 200   x-routed-to=spark-connect-tenant-b
            server response: Spark Connect request completed without asserting a user_id that matches the verified principal 'tenant_b'
cert 'agent_a':  HTTP 200   x-routed-to=DENIED
            server response: no tenant route for this principal%0A

no client cert:  http_code=000 (000 => TLS handshake refused: require_client_certificate)
TLS handshake refused (no client cert)

VERDICT: the authenticated principal (client-cert SAN), not the client's choice, selects the tenant
server. A tenant_a cert reaches ONLY spark-connect-tenant-a (its interceptor echoes principal
'tenant_a'); tenant_b -> spark-connect-tenant-b; an un-granted principal -> 403 DENIED; no cert -> refused.
